{
  "texts": [
    "Train a freshly loaded, pretrained LM on the n unlabeled texts in extra using the LM's pretraining objective-masked language modeling loss for BERT, or causal language modeling loss for GPT-2.",
    "Texts are passed independently, and padded to form batches.",
    "Add a linear layer to this model and finetune all of the LM's weights to minimize classification cross entropy loss on train.",
    "Step 1 is task-adaptive pretraining-a procedure broadly recommended by Gururangan et al. (2020).",
    "Step 2 is a canonical way to train a transformerbased LM for a classification task, according to Section 2 of Zhang et al. (2021)."
  ]
}